<paragraph id="8BC93698FFB274475B83F90F222C3DEC" blockId="29.[155,770,1698,1904]" lastBlockId="29.[819,1434,1698,1751]" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis id="B902EA8AFFB274475B83F90F27203D8D" box="[155,262,1698,1719]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">Remarks:</emphasis>
This is the second record in the east Pacific Ocean after its original description. Our specimens were collected in the 
<typeStatus id="54CD883AFFB274475AA7F94D27D63DCF" box="[447,496,1760,1781]" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">type</typeStatus>
locality of Mazatlán (
<collectingRegion id="49B2F87AFFB274475BBAF95326DC3C2E" box="[162,250,1790,1812]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">Sinaloa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3617608FFB274475A11F953277A3C2E" box="[265,348,1790,1812]" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">Mexico</collectingCountry>
), and they perfectly match with the original Hancock description. Along the Atlantic coast of South America specimens without microrhabds and with a violet colour have been cited, which must not be considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D1BFFB2744758AFF90E22553D82" authorityName="Rosell &amp; Uriz" authorityYear="1997" box="[951,1139,1699,1720]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Pione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clionaida" pageId="29" pageNumber="382" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="carpenteri">
<emphasis id="B902EA8AFFB2744758AFF90E22553D82" box="[951,1139,1699,1720]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">Pione carpenteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B69FFB274475F9EF90F23513D8D" author="Boury-Esnault N" box="[1158,1399,1698,1720]" pageId="29" pageNumber="382" pagination="263 - 295" refId="ref23809" refString="Boury-Esnault N. 1973. Resultats Scientifiques des Campagnes de la Calypso. Campagne de la Calypso au large des cotes atlantiques de l'amerique du sud (1961 - 62). I. 29. Spongiaires. Annals de l'Institute Oceanographic 49: 263 - 295." type="journal article" year="1973">Boury-Esnault, 1973</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D1BFFB27447582BF96C25DC3DED" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1867" box="[819,1018,1729,1751]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Cliona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clionaida" pageId="29" pageNumber="382" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="carpenteri">
<emphasis id="B902EA8AFFB27447582BF96C25DC3DED" box="[819,1018,1729,1751]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="382">Cliona carpenteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
